abstract: >
  Kappa-FIN applies the Kappa Method — persistent homology H₁ of rolling
  correlation networks (Spearman + Ledoit-Wolf shrinkage) combined with
  Forman-Ricci curvature — to detect systemic risk precursors in financial
  markets weeks to months before crises materialize. The system uses two
  complementary criteria: the Rayleigh criterion (Ohio Number Oh(t), derived
  from H₁ topological mass relative to a CALM baseline) and the Prandtl
  criterion (structural memory Φ(t), a leaky integrator with γ=0.985 of
  negative curvature accumulation). Dual crossing detection with automated
  CALM baseline identification (KCPT anti-contamination penalty) avoids
  false positives from exogenous shocks. Demonstrated case study: ~60-day
  lead time on the 2008 Global Financial Crisis; correct negative on
  COVID-19 exogenous shock. Part of the Kappa Method ecosystem validating
  the Law of Ohio (Organized Hallucination In Optimization) across financial
  markets, LLMs, and educational systems.

keywords:
  - topological data analysis
  - persistent homology
